        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We aim to maximize the continuum sensitivity of our observations -- this drives the proposed setting of the SPWs. At these frequencies, we will be able to encompass the CO(10-9) line (and possibly other fainter ISM tracers) in the QSO host galaxy. The CO(3-2) line in the Slug has a width of ~200 km/s. We opt for a 4-channel binning in order to lower the data rate.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_CORRELATOR</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We aim to map the dust emission in the Slug in band 7. A 7-pointing mosaic, combined with ACA observations is required in order to cover the entire nebula, which extends over ~40" (see Fig.1). We opt for the most compact array configuration (C36-1) in order to minimize spatial filtering. This will yield a resolution element of 1".</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_ANGULAR_RESOLUTION</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We aim to detect dust emission associated with diffuse star formation in the nebula. Our sensitivity (1 sigma) per beam will be 60 uJy (L_IR=1.4e10 Lsun), corresponding to a dust mass sensitivity of only ~1e5 Msun per beam or an approximate SFR sensitivity of ~2 Msun/yr. This limit matches the constrain on the surface density of molecular gas, Sigma_gas&lt;60 Msun/pc2, set by our PdBI observations (see Fig.2). </prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_SENSITIVITY</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
